 ===new django project===
 django-admin startproject <projectname>
 
 
 ===activate virtual env===
 source ~/.virtualenvs/djangodev/bin/activate
 
 ===start dev server===
 python3 manage.py runserver
 
 
===make new app in django project===
python3 manage.py startpp <appname>

===basic process for making new app===
1. make app as listed above

2. create view

3. add app url

4. add app url to project

5. migrate: "python3 manage.py migrate"

6. add app to installed apps

7. python3 manage.py makemigrations my_app


===templates===

must be in this format <project>/<app_name>/"templates"/<app_name>/<file>.html

==django template tags and filters===
- similar to data annotations
- https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/ref/templates/builtins/


===static files===
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/howto/static-files/

in the settings.py file under the STATIC_URL variable


===sqlite===
https://www.sqlite.org/whentouse.html

===model fields===
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/topics/db/models/


===migrations===
manage.py make migrations <appname>: stages migrations but does not run them against the db

manage.py migrate: runs existing migrations

manage.py sqlmigrate app 0001: shows actual sql query

steps for migrations:
	1. initial project migrate command
	2. create app and create models
	3. register app in INSTALLED_APPS in settings.py
	4. Run makemigrations for new app
	5. Rune migrate for new migrations



===save to db===
1. create instance of object
2. <object>.save()

or

<class_name>.objects.create(<properties>)

or

create objects in bulk:

<class_name>.objects.bulk_create(mylist)


==query docs===
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/topics/db/queries/


===get() and filter()===

get() is good for a single record

===Q===
Q object. Allows you to use boolean logic


===field_lookup===
special syntax for more advanced searches
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/ref/models/querysets/


===model field validators===
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.0/ref/validators/


===model deafults and validation===
use defaults when possible:
heartrate = models.IntegerField(default=60, validators=[MinValueValidator(1),MaxValueValidator(300)])

===update==
query for object
save into a variable
variable.property = new property
save to db



==form csrf token===
needs {% csrf_token %} tag


